          <div class="article-intro">
            <p class="lead">If you own an investment property in the Greater Toronto Area and are considering listing it on Airbnb, there's one critical rule you need to understand: the <strong>principal residence requirement</strong>. In most GTA cities, you cannot short-term rent a property unless you actually live there.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="principal-residence">The Principal Residence Rule</h2>
          <p>Most municipalities in the GTA have implemented short-term rental regulations that include a <strong>principal residence requirement</strong>. This means:</p>

          <div class="callout callout-warning">
            <div class="callout-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"></path>
